description:
Many are expecting the kingdom of God on earth to be set up very soon. But could this earthly kingdom be a deception? This video presents information to help people understand why Jesus said, in answer to the question about His Second Coming, “Be careful that no one deceives you.” Professor Walter J. Veith shows how the devil has managed to hide his identity and to deceive people into believing that the kingdom he is setting up is the kingdom of God. 

Vatican II outlined a new direction for the church. It was this council that made it possible for Protestant churches to be gathered back into the Roman Catholic Church. But how was this made possible? Did the Catholic Church reform its doctrines to come in line with Biblical teachings? Has Rome changed? Was Vatican II a breath of fresh air, as many Protestants believe or was it instead, the greatest deception ever perpetrated on humanity? 

What new theology has infiltrated the Christian church in recent years to cause Christians to forget Biblical teachings? Is it true, as proponents of The Seven Mountains Initiative believe, that when the church controls business, government, media, arts and entertainment, education, family, and religion that the kingdom of God and the millennium of peace will be ushered in? Why have all the recent popes been asking for a new world order? Where did these new ideas come from? 

If Jesus Christ was willing to die to give us freedom of choice, so that we could choose to serve Him out of love, how can we allow antichrist to rob us of the right to freedom of choice? The Bible tells us that when Satan’s kingdom is set up in this world and he makes a final move to eradicate God’s people, those who live by His Word, then Christ will come. We have a choice: to give up our God-given right to freedom of choice, or to accept that Christ died to give us free choice, and honor Him through obedience. 

Discover more: http://amazingdiscoveries.org/
